RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 78. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: O'BANION (IRE) stalked the solid early pace between runners, lost ground along the turn and chased two wide to the quarter marker, was steered four then five wide into the stretch and made a mild gain at the furlong marker, responded to urging into the final sixteenth, overtook HAVAKASH READY and edged away in deep stretch to prevail. HAVAKASH READY showed good early speed and set a fast pace into the turn, drew to a clear lead while carving out solid fractions heading to the quarter pole, was set down in upper stretch and showed the way to the furloing marker, held foes at bay to the sixteenth-pole, was overtaken by O'BANION in deep stretch and was outfinished for the win, while besting the rest. HE'S INIT TO WINIT tracked the solid pace from the inside, lost ground along the turn and chased to the quarter marker, maintained an inside path into the stretch and re-rallied at the furlong grounds, was outkicked in the final sixteenth and just held for third. SMOKIN' GOOD TIME raced a bit in tight early on, saved ground into the turn and improved position at the quarter marker, angled four wide into the stretch, was gaining in the final furlong and just missed for third. JAIME'S COMMITMENT chased the solid pace from a two wide position and offered a mild late rally. AS LUCK HAPPENS close up early, chased the loose pacesetter to the quarter marker, ran in pursuit to mid-stretch and gave way. GALLO DEL CIELO showed brief speed, lost position four wide on the turn, swung five wide for the drive and weakened. HOLY SMOKES lacked early speed, chased from the rail along the turn and did not factor. UNCLE DUSAN chased the fast early pace from mid-pack, was coaxed along three wide to the quarter marker, dropped back into the stretch and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GONNA GETCHA GOOD tracked the solid early pace from the inside, was well positioned along the turn while saving ground, roused into upper stretch and vied for the lead heading to the furlong marker, took a narrow inside of the furlong pole and battled determinedly into the final sixteenth, held foes at bay into deep stretch and kept to task in the final strides to prevail. RUTHERFORD tracked the solid early pace from the outside, gave chase two wide along the turn, tipped three wide into the stretch and raced within aim approaching the furlong marker, battled into the final sixteenth, was outkicked by the winner in deep stretch and held well in the final strides to secure second. ALMOST SNOW broke alertly and took back to track the fast early pace, was guided three wide into the turn and tracked to the quarter marker, was roused three wide into the stretch and vied for the lead approaching the furlong grounds, battled into the final sixteenth, was outfinished in deep stretch and was denied for second at the wire. YOU ENJOY MYSELF bumped at the start and was off a bit slowly, chased the solid pace from the inside and raced a bit in tight at the quarter marker, tipped two wide into the stretch then shifted three wide at the furlong grounds, was gaining in the late stages but could not reel in the leaders in deep stretch. MY BUCKET LIST chased three wide in the early going, swung five wide into upper stretch and ran evenly to the furlong marker, needed more in the final sixteenth and offered a mild late rally. DRAW SOME chased from a two wide path in the early stages, made a mild gain into the stretch and finished evenly. BAILS HIM OUT chased from the second flight, raced four wide to the quarter marker and did not threaten in the stretch. GOOD FOCUS showed good early speed, dictated terms while carving out solid fractions, came under pressure at mid-stretch and faded in the final furlong. WESTERN CAPE chased the solid early pace outside of runners, drifted out a bit while navigating the turn and raced four wide to the quarter marker, saved ground into the stretch and did not factor.

STREET TIGER away in good order, was prominent leaving the break and contested the solid early pace with PONDERGATING, set contested fractions into the turn and was well handled while carving a moderate pace to the quarter pole, shook free into the stretch and was asked for more at the furlong marker, was overtaken by BROOKYS GAL inside of the sixteenth-pole and was gamely bested in deep stretch, while holding well in the end for second. HOT AND SPICY never far back, tracked the early pace from the inside, came in tight entering the turn and waited for racing room at the quarter marker, shifted to the outside into upper stretch then angled five to six wide at the furlong marker, finished well in deep stretch and missed for second while holding safely in the end for third. SHADOWED THOUGHTS close up in the early stages, tracked the decent pace three wide along the turn, tipped four wide for the drive and battled to mid-stretch, fought into the final sixteenth and was outkicked in deep stretch. ETHAN'S GIRL off slowly and spotted the field to begin, rushed up outside of rivals and improved position five wide at the quarter pole, maintained a five wide path into the stretch and gained ground to come within aim at the furlong marker, needed more in the final sixteenth and gave way in deep stretch. PONDERGATING hustled away from the start, engaged with STREET TIGER in the early going and dueled through solid fractions heading to the turn, pressed outside of STREET TIGER to the quarter pole, battled into the stretch and chased STREET TIGER to mid-stretch, could not keep pace into the final sixteenth and weakened late. CHAMAVILLE chased outside of runners to begin, improved position four wide at the quarter pole, swung to the six path into upper stretch and lost ground at the furlong marker, lacked a response in deep stretch and finished evenly. PRINCESS K chased from the rear early on, raced a bit in tight heading into the turn, chased two wide to the quarter marker and did not threaten in the stretch. BABY I'M A STAR chased the pace from the inside, saved ground into the stretch, was outrun to the furlong pole and tired in the final stages. BUENISIMO was slow into stride despite the best efforts of the rider, went three wide into the first turn then rated mid-pack until the far turn, launched a bid after passing the three furlong marker, swung out five wide into the stretch and was between horses in a three-way battle for second and got a nose in front at the wire. ECOLOGIST was pushed from the gate into the early mix then was being ridden down the backstretch run to keep up with the pace, went into a full drive from the three furlong pole and responded with a good finish but was out-nodded for the place. GALLANT WARREN was allowed to settle into stride from the break, stayed along the rail down the backstretch making steady forward progress to the far turn, was right behind the leading pair passing the five-sixteenths marker then had to wait for room, got a fortunate inside run into the stretch, then was inside of a three horse battle down the stretch for the place and came up just short. DESERT DUDE broke in and made light contact with WELLSWORT (IRE) then was hustled to get forward position going into the turn, then was content to sit behind the leading pair to the far turn, got closer through that turn then was set down near the quarter pole, loomed a threat to mid-stretch then weakened in the final furlong. ATTENZIONE unhurried early, settled near the rear of the field in the early going racing off the rail in the three to four path, tried to make a wide rally through the far turn then came extremely wide into the stretch, kept to task but could only pass a couple of stragglers late. WELLSWORT (IRE) took a light bump from DESERT DUDE after the break, lacked early speed and moved over to the rail when clear, held that position to the far turn, was roused approaching the stretch but could do no better than chase to the wire. BRONZE WARRIOR was hustled and easily gained the early lead then was allowed to set moderate fractions with AUSPICIOUS STYLE stalking to the outside but not pressing the issue, had no response when that rival took over the lead passing the five-sixteenths marker, came under pressure before the quarter pole and hand nothing to offer down the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 10 1M All Weather Track CR: 89. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROISTER broke sharply but veered in and made light contact with MY SUNSHINE, seized the early lead, took the field through comfortable fractions while keep all at bay to the stretch, quickened when set down passing the three-sixteenth pole, drew away and won geared down near the wire. BEROLIJEAN (FR) broke a step slow then was rushed up into contention, floated six wide into the clubhouse turn, pulled the rider up close to the early leaders down the backstretch, made an eye-catching move four wide through the far turn, was outkicked in the final furlong and held well in the end for second. WILL IS CHILL checked hard off heels going into the first turn and was forced out to the five or six path, made slow but steady progress from the rear of the field to get into contention, bid in earnest from the three furlong pole, came into the stretch six wide and produced a grinding finish that was good enough to gain the show. WALKING BOSS was content to save ground near the rear of the field, mounted a rally into traffic on the far turn, then swung seven wide into the stretch and closed willingly but was to late to crack the top three. LIFESBEENGOODSOFAR was keen to get into the early mix and was caught four wide around the first turn, pulled to a position just behind the trio contesting the early pace, was content to hold that position down the backstretch, became boxed in through the far turn, then ran on evenly when clear in the late stages. POUR ON THE COLE checked hard going into the first turn, was content to keep the inside path through the early stages, started to make a run then had to check slightly near the three furlong pole, idled behind a wall of horses to the stretch, had clear run passing the three-sixteenths pole but was unable to tae advantage and tired. LORD WIMBORNE (IRE) lumbered away from the gate well behind the field, then got over to the rail before the first bend, settled in the rear for the first half mile, tried to make an eight wide run into the stretch but was unable to make an impact. AWESOME DUDE settled mid-pack while racing two deep early, pulled close to the leaders down the backstretch, checked in traffic twice in the far turn, got clear in the stretch but was unable to make an impact. MY SUNSHINE brushed with ROISTER at the break then while trying to contest the early pace put POUR ON THE COLE in tight going into the first turn, switched out a path and stalked the pacesetting ROISTER from two deep, remained prominent to the far turn, then came under pressure near the five-sixteenths marker and weakened. BROOKYS TAPIT got away well then pressed the pace three wide under a firm hold, remained close through the far turn then began to struggle to keep up passing the five-sixteenth pole and came up empty in the stretch.
